, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9136] upgraded polars to 0.28
tesla232 added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9143] span fixes during duration conversion
zhiburt made fixes to 
``explore``
: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9139] nu-explore: Fix repeated char issue in cmdline
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9137] nu-explore: Fix pipeline rendering
amtoine 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9138] swapped the date and the log level in the 
``std log``
 format
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9135] FEATURE: add a 
``main``
 command to 
``toolkit.nu``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9115] REFACTOR: make 
``input list``
 a tiny bit tighter
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9101] FIX: have consistent errors between 
``std help``
 and 
``std help ...``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9100] REFACTOR: fix typos and simplify external 
``std help``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9074] FIX: add a space after the default left prompt
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/8406] REFACTOR: move the banner from the 
``rust``
 source to the standard library
1Kinoti 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9129] added more commands to 
``std iter``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/8958] improve error when name and parameters are not space-separated
kubouch made lots of module fixes: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9125] Reuse parsed modules
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9121] Fix exported module not found
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9066] Allow creating modules from directories
melMass 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9097] enabled setup-git-hooks on windows
EmilySeville7cfg created 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9091] FEATURE: format 
``std log``
 and add 
``--short``
 option
stevenxxiu added a fix: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9053] use 
``buffer.len()``
 instead of 
``cursor_pos``
, so the 
``.expect()``
 isn't useless
